<subSubSection pageId="33" pageNumber="123" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="33.[189,302,933,959]" box="[189,302,933,959]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,302,933,959]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,302,933,959]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="33.[188,1400,979,1217]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">
Lallemand in 1927 described this species based on the pattern of coloration and placed it in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1901" box="[1271,1391,980,1005]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Mioscarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1271,1391,980,1005]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Mioscarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. He mentioned only a single male specimen (
<typeStatus box="[704,813,1015,1042]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">holotype</typeStatus>
), however, in the collection it is labelled as female (
<figureCitation box="[197,306,1050,1077]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="34.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[193,1397,512,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-80@34.[189,1398,512,1923]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Fig. 15. Trigonoschema pallida (Lallemand, 1927) comb. nov., holotype (NHMUK 013588933), habitus. A. Lateral view. B. Frontal view. C. Dorsal view. D. Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705024/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Fig. 15D</figureCitation>
). This species does not conform to Breddin’s definition of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Breddin" authorityYear="1901" box="[989,1110,1051,1076]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Mioscarta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[989,1110,1051,1076]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Mioscarta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but possesses characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="For" authorityName="Crispolon &amp; Guilbert &amp; Yap &amp; Soulier-Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[222,403,1085,1111]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Trigonoschema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[222,403,1085,1111]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Trigonoschema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[411,520,1086,1112]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
For this reason we transfer it to this new genus. We could not borrow the 
<typeStatus box="[190,296,1120,1146]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">holotype</typeStatus>
, however some photographs of the habitus and labels were kindly provided by Mick Webb (NHM). They are integrated here (
<figureCitation box="[612,701,1155,1182]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="34.[189,232,1962,1988]" captionTargetBox="[193,1397,512,1867]" captionTargetId="figure-80@34.[189,1398,512,1923]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Fig. 15. Trigonoschema pallida (Lallemand, 1927) comb. nov., holotype (NHMUK 013588933), habitus. A. Lateral view. B. Frontal view. C. Dorsal view. D. Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5705024" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5705024/files/figure.png" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) and are sufficient to see the most obvious characters of 
<taxonomicName authority="Crispolon &amp; Guilbert &amp; Yap &amp; Soulier-Perkins, 2021" authorityName="Crispolon &amp; Guilbert &amp; Yap &amp; Soulier-Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,370,1191,1217]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Trigonoschema" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,370,1191,1217]" italics="true" pageId="33" pageNumber="123">Trigonoschema</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[377,484,1191,1217]" pageId="33" pageNumber="123" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
